replies.body:
I was just about to hit thirty and wanted to try jungling, so I decided to pick up Nautilus. He was big, stompy, tanky, and a total bad ass, so I was sold. I began playing as a jungler more and found him to still be fun no matter what I was doing, as he always felt like all his abilities were about keeping people under your boot while being so big and terrifying they couldn't stop you. To this day I've stuck with Naut as my main jungler even though I don't really main any role, just because I still have fun with him. 

Ain't no meta gonna tell me when to play or not play Nautilus!

{{champion:111}}

I think I'm one of very few whose first main champion was Taric. Before even playing League, I knew that I would like to play support over any other role (and I still do), but I needed a champion that was fairly cheap to level up with. My friends told me to get Taric because he was decent (at the time) and was a fairly low cost. I thought the idea of an on-target stun was super good, so I stuck with him for a while. Ultimately, I came to know that he was outclassed by a few other supports (Thresh, Leona, Janna, and Sona were pretty big at the time). So, I ultimately bought Leona and didn't play Taric much since, though there was always a place in my heart for the Gem Knight.

When Pre-season 4 rolled around, Taric turned out to be practically broken, so I returned to playing him for that whole period of time. Sadly, his ratios were nerfed because of it, and I have seldom played him since Season 4 started. Nevertheless, he remains to be one of my favorite champions of all time to play. One of my favorite things to do nowadays is Taric Top (:

